  "text": "The length L SA is 0.03 m [CITATION_1] and the radius r SA is 0.002 m, therefore we find R SA = 14,323,945 Pa s m , though, DP = (R RA + R TSA ) Q = 178 Pa. So the pressure difference drops by 1.4% between the entry of the kidney and the artery at which the geometry of the model begins.",
